<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Coucou</title>
</head>
<body>
  <{let x = 3 let f = fun x -> x > 2}>
  <h1>Real globals</h1>
  <p>
    x: <{x}><br/>
    f: <{f}>
  </p>
  <h1>Globals within HTML within ML</h1>
  <h2>Scoped:</h2>
  <p>
    <{
      <[
        <{
          let x = 41
          let f = fixfun g x -> g (x + 1)
        }>
        x: <{x}><br/>
        f: <{f}>
        <{
          let x = 32 in
          <[coucouc <{x}> coucou]>
        }>
      ]>
    }>
  </p>
  <h2>But outside the outer ML brackets, it remains</h2>
  <p>
    x: <{x}><br/>
    f: <{f}>
  </p>
</body>
</html>